    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="2OCOgk"&gt;Anker &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/7/24215215/anker-prime-charger-usb-c-gan-power"&gt;announced several additions&lt;/a&gt; to the company’s Prime line of chargers today, including a new desktop version that allows the power output of its six USB ports to be customized through a control dial. As a result, connected devices get exactly as much power as they need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="NXR0k4"&gt;The new $169.99 &lt;a href="https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;amp;xs=1&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.anker.com%2Fproducts%2Fa2345-anker-prime-charger-250w-6-ports-ganprime%3Fvariant%3D43931956478102&amp;amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F8%2F7%2F24215376%2Fanker-prime-charger-desktop-usb-c-gan-power" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;Anker Prime Charger&lt;/a&gt; shares 250W of power across four USB-C ports and two USB-A ports. The first USB-C port can deliver up to 140W of power, while the other three max out at 100W. The two USB-A ports deliver up to 22.5W each.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;figure class="e-image"&gt;
        
      &lt;cite&gt;Image: Anker&lt;/cite&gt;
      &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;em&gt;An LCD screen shows the power output of each USB-C port.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;
  &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p id="qz15RO"&gt;The charger offers four different power distribution modes, adjustable through a built-in control dial or Anker’s mobile app. &lt;/p&gt;
