    <title>Senators want an investigation of the Fox-Disney-Warner Bros. sports bundle</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="Sen. Elizabeth Warren (D-MA)" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/IA4wWN6mkSDnB50KPkoe6G2tOyU=/0x0:4941x3294/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73507271/2160975539.0.jpg" /&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="ua3Uot"&gt;A new joint venture between three streaming leaders could create a monopoly problem in sports television, three lawmakers warn US regulators &lt;a href="https://www.warren.senate.gov/imo/media/doc/warren_castro_letter_to_doj_and_fcc_re_sports_streaming_jv.pdf"&gt;in a letter&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5685739/2024/08/07/dept-of-justice-disney-fox-warner-bros-tnt/?redirected=1"&gt;first reported by &lt;em&gt;The Athletic&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="IwMJOk"&gt;Sens. Elizabeth Warren (D-MA) and Bernie Sanders (I-VT) and Rep. Joaquin Castro (D-TX) are asking&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;law enforcers to investigate the joint venture between Disney, Fox, and Warner Bros. to create a new service, Venu Sports. The streaming service is &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/6/24064007/espn-fox-warner-bros-sports-streaming-partnership"&gt;expected to include sports networks&lt;/a&gt; from across the three companies’ portfolios, including ESPN, Fox, and TNT. Last week, the companies announced that Venu Sports &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/1/24211138/venu-sports-disney-fox-warner-bros-discovery-pricing"&gt;will cost $42.99 per month&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
